<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Private equity recruiting notoriously happens =
roughly two years in advance: People get hired at investment banks as analy=
sts, start their two-year analyst program, and more or less immediately sta=
rt interviewing for private equity jobs to start at the end of the analyst =
program. The thinking is, roughly:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The banks do a decent job of=C2=A0<em>=
selecting=C2=A0</em>people, so if the PE firms hire from a pool of bank ana=
lysts they will get good employees.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">The banks do a decent job of=C2=A0<em>training=C2=A0</em>people, so if th=
e analysts finish their two-year analyst program before starting in PE they=
 will know what they are doing.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">No=
body is going to distinguish themselves=C2=A0<em>all that much=C2=A0</em>as=
 a banking analyst: The PE firms don=E2=80=99t need to wait until the end o=
f the analyst program to hire the analysts who did the best job; they can j=
ust hire the analysts they like the most at the beginning of the program, a=
nd figure they will all get the same basic training and experience.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The earlier you hire, the better your sel=
ection will be, so if your competitors are hiring in October you hire in Se=
ptember, and the hiring keeps getting earlier and earlier.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In principle the earliest possible date for pr=
ivate equity recruiting would be, like, the day after college seniors get t=
heir offers at investment banks, but in practice recruiting seems to happen=
 around the time the analysts=C2=A0<em>start=C2=A0</em>their banking jobs, =
not when they=C2=A0<em>get=C2=A0</em>them. This year <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31871501.256403/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMjIvcHJpdmF0ZS1lcXVpdHktcy1yYWNlLXR=
vLXBvYWNoLWp1bmlvci1iYW5rZXJzLWZpbmRzLWl0cy1saW1pdD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjIyMjNfTU=
9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVyb=
T0yMzA2MjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB99f1170=
6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  that was too early though</a>?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Private equity shops looking to fill out their=
 2024 associate classes were forced to do a second round of recruiting this=
 year after initial efforts fell short, according to an analysis by recruit=
er Odyssey Search Partners.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Eager to beat competitors, many buyout shops s=
tarted reaching out to banks=E2=80=99 first-year trainees just a few weeks =
after they began work in 2022. But the newly arrived dealmakers, dubbed ana=
lysts, weren=E2=80=99t quite ready to boast about their prowess. Some had y=
et to complete a single deal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CMany of Wall Street=E2=80=99s promine=
nt institutions were left with unfilled positions,=E2=80=9D according to th=
e Odyssey report. =E2=80=9CFrom the perspective of many investment banking =
analysts, the acceleration of recruiting timelines has reduced their willin=
gness and ability to participate.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Back in 2010, private equity firms typically w=
aited for junior bankers to soak up about 11 months of training before poac=
hing efforts started. For the associate class of 2024, private equity giant=
s began recruiting less than a month into their program. That was the earli=
est kickoff to on-cycle recruiting ever, Odyssey found.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CMany analysts during the on-cycle per=
iod in August 2022 held off,=E2=80=9D the Odyssey report found. =E2=80=9CTo=
 do well, bankers typically believe they should have closed at least one tr=
ansaction in order to have material to discuss in interviews. The slower M&=
amp;A environment has reduced their level of experience compared to that of=
 prior classes.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s adorable? A downstream effect o=
f a slower M&amp;A environment is that first-month investment banking analy=
sts have never closed a deal,=C2=A0so they don=E2=80=99t feel like they hav=
e anything to talk about at PE recruiting, so they don=E2=80=99t do it, so =
PE firms can=E2=80=99t hire junior associates, so they can=E2=80=99t close =
more deals, further slowing the M&amp;A environment? I am not at all sure w=
hy first-month investment bankers would =E2=80=9Cbelieve they should have c=
losed at least one transaction in order to have material to discuss in inte=
rviews=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0I cannot believe that a first-month banker=
=E2=80=99s prowess at deal closing would be material in a PE firm=E2=80=99s=
 hiring decisions =E2=80=94 but here we are.</p>
