#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> knew what sh=
e was getting into</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter Chief Executive Linda Yaccarino interv=
ened to help repair the relationship between the social-media company and A=
lphabet=E2=80=99s Google after a payment issue, a person familiar with the =
matter said, an early example of the new CEO=E2=80=99s management style.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter is now paying Google for its cloud ser=
vices after not consistently paying some of those bills, people familiar wi=
th the matter said. Those bills amounted to more than $20 million a month r=
ecently, people familiar with the matter said. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter and Google have had significant busine=
ss ties. Twitter has used Google=E2=80=99s cloud services for a range of pu=
rposes, including anti-spam technology and data-warehousing services, accor=
ding to people familiar with the matter and past blog posts from both compa=
nies. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter=E2=80=99s spending on Google=E2=80=99s=
 cloud services became a focus internally at Twitter after Twitter owner El=
on Musk acquired the company late last year and quickly placed an emphasis =
on cutting costs and curbing reliance on vendors, according to people famil=
iar with the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Under Musk=E2=80=99s ownership, Twitter has be=
en accused of missing payments on some bills that Musk inherited when he to=
ok over and implemented a more austere spending style.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe new CEO=E2=80=99s management styl=
e=E2=80=9D is that when big vendors send her a bill for services that they =
provided as agreed and that are critical to Twitter=E2=80=99s functioning, =
she pays it. This was also the management style of Twitter=E2=80=99s previo=
us CEOs, except one of them.</p>
